✨T𝕒𝕣𝕠𝕥 R𝕖𝕧𝕖𝕒𝕝 ✨ 
1. The Moon is a reminder not to take everything at face value. Sometimes we only know half a story and don’t have all the information you need to move forward. Listen to your intuition so you can see beyond what’s in front of you. Feel into situations rather thinking what they mean. Let go of negative self talk and allow your intuition to guide you and give you a greater level of understanding. Feel into situations rather than overthinking what they might mean. Pay attention to your dreams, they can also give you guidance about which direction to go. 

2. The Nine of Cups is often known as the wish card as it’s an excellent omen that the things you’re working towards will soon come to fruition. Keep using your intentions to work towards your goal. Remember that what you put into the Universe, you receive, so keep a positive approach and this energy will be returned to you through success and fulfilment. This card is also a reminder to count your blessings and be consciously grateful for the people in your life. Overtime, this will help to intensify feelings of contentment as well as your ability to attract what you wish for. You attract what you give.

3. The Two of Pentacles suggests you are currently juggling many different responsibilities and you’re struggling to manage them all together. There’s lots on your mind and this card asks you to manage your time and priorities carefully. It’s about trying to achieve some sort of balance so you can also get some down time. You may be losing sight of the bigger picture and instead you get lost and stressed out by the little details. You need to stop and step back for a while so you can explore and ask yourself what you actually want from life. Sometimes taking a break can be the most productive thing you can do so you can reassess your responsibilities and priorities.

The New Moon is coming up on September 7, in the zodiac sign of Virgo. 

One of the major themes is healing, particularly from things from our childhoods that still effects us today but no longer serves us. This could be beliefs, feelings, emotions or behaviours that could be limiting or stopping our growth and stopping us from moving forwards. It’s time to let go. 

As an Earth sign, Virgo is a reminder that keeping ourselves grounded at this time is so important in order to support us through this process.

Are you ready?!

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
🌿 F𝕠𝕣𝕒𝕘𝕚𝕟𝕘 🌿
Foraging is an under rated practice. It’s great because you can find so many free spell ingredients, even if you live in an urban area. This makes it great if you’re a Witch on a budget! I know I don’t have the money to spend on expensive spell ingredients, but there is so much you can forage for yourself. You’ll probably be surprised what’s growing near you. 

The beauty of foraging regularly is it really aligns you to the seasons and the seasonal changes. Also, any excuse to get out into nature and tune yourself into her rhythms is always a good thing! There’s also something special and satisfying about finding your own herbs and using them in your Craft.

The app ‘Seek’ makes it easy to identify plants/herbs. And it’s completely free! As a side note, this app will help identify the poisonous plants to help you avoid the ones that can cause harm or even death. But don’t necessarily rely on the app alone. The Encyclopaedia of Magical Herbs by Scott Cunningham is my go-to book for identifying herbs.

🚫 NEVER consume or put any herbs on your skin that you don’t know the identification of - even the most ordinary looking plants can be toxi. If in doubt, leave it out! 🌿🍃

Do you forage? What growing in your local area?

Lindsay 💜

✨ S𝕖𝕝𝕗 C𝕒𝕣𝕖 O𝕣𝕒𝕔𝕝𝕖 R𝕖𝕧𝕖𝕒𝕝 ✨ 
1. A𝕣𝕠𝕞𝕒𝕥𝕙𝕖𝕣𝕒𝕡𝕪
Aromatherapy is a powerful tool to connect with flowers, plants and the wider natural world. Pay attention to how each different smell makes you feel and what emotions or memories they trigger. Try anointing yourself with your favourite oil on your wrists or throat. Try using a diffuser at home with an oil that promotes peace and happiness or one at work that helps productivity.

2. S𝕪𝕟𝕔 𝕨𝕚𝕥𝕙 𝕥𝕙𝕖 M𝕠𝕠𝕟
The moon is a powerful celestial body that reflects the flow of our lives and the phases we go through. With the new moon coming up, it’s a great time to reconnect. The new moon signifies new beginnings so is the start of the moons month long cycle. Start following the different phases of the moon as you move through the next 30 days. Research how the energies of the different phases can be used in you own life. 

3. C𝕣𝕖𝕒𝕥𝕖 A𝕣𝕥
We’re all artists, creators of the lives we leading. Look for opportunities to create art for your own pleasure. We all have our very different creative aspects of our character so this art will be different to everyone. We can be creative with our words and actions and it doesn’t have to be art in its most common form like painting and drawing. Feel into which artistic modality will allow you to express yourself.

🪐 P𝕝𝕒𝕟𝕖𝕥𝕤 & P𝕖𝕣𝕤𝕠𝕟𝕒𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕪 🪐
Most western horoscopes are based on our Sun sign, otherwise know as our star sign. But have you ever wondered what the other signs in your chart mean? 

The big three are your sun, moon and rising signs, but other planets and signs in your birth chart can tell you a lot about yourself and your personality too.

If you don’t know about your birth chart, there are loads of birth chart calculators out there online. All you need is the date and location of your birth as well as the time you were born.

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
I’ve been putting this off because speaking about it makes it more real, but I know I can’t put it off or pretend things are ok forever. Salem crossed the rainbow bridge 15 days ago. He was hit by a car that left him at the side of the road. The only good thing is that it was quick and he didn’t suffer. I helped him come into this world, he was my baby.
My heart is broken. 

Luna and Merlin are learning to adjust. I gave them time with Salem to say their own goodbyes as they need space to grieve in their own ways too 💔 The dynamics of the relationship between them has changed - Luna is being much nicer to Merlin to the point where they fell asleep together on the bed. They have never done that before.

Today, I welcome his ashes home. I’ve made a small altar ready from him in the sitting room where he can still be at the heart of family life. Wait for me at the rainbow bridge my angel. 💔

Lindsay 💜

UPDATE: 
Thank you for all your kind messages. Your energy and love coming from all around the world is truly appreciated, I know I don’t bear this alone. I’ll try to answer your DMs when I feel ready and able. Much love 💜

✨B𝕒𝕝𝕒𝕟𝕔𝕚𝕟𝕘 R𝕠𝕠𝕞 S𝕡𝕣𝕒𝕪✨
This makes a beautiful smelling spray that helps to cleanse and balance the energies of any area. Sprays are an easy way to change the energy of a space. They are also handy for putting a small spray bottle to carry with you for when you need them.

You can use dried/fresh herbs as well as essential oils. Using essential oils will give you a spray that is longer lasting and all you need is a few drops of each oil, diluted in a bottle full of water to make them safe.

If you use fresh or fired herbs, the mix will last between 2-3 weeks before they will start to go all soft.
You can use moon water if you have any but tap or bottled water is fine to use too.

Lindsay 💜
